WEBVTT

1
00:03:20.576 --> 00:03:22.077
Agojie! Agoj...

2
00:04:10.209 --> 00:04:11.210
No!

3
00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:31.897
Where are the prisoners?

4
00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:33.607
Where are our people?

5
00:04:33.690 --> 00:04:36.068
We are farmers. We took no one!

6
00:04:36.568 --> 00:04:37.568
<i>Miganon.</i>

7
00:05:07.850 --> 00:05:09.309
You will be home soon.

8
00:05:28.579 --> 00:05:29.788
Horses.

9
00:05:32.666 --> 00:05:34.918
That can only mean Oyo soldiers.

10
00:05:47.514 --> 00:05:48.891
Who is she?

11
00:05:50.809 --> 00:05:52.102
My mother.

12
00:05:52.728 --> 00:05:56.106
We will take you back to your
village. Perhaps your father...

13
00:05:56.190 --> 00:05:57.274
They sold him.

14
00:05:58.567 --> 00:05:59.985
And my brothers.

15
00:06:01.320 --> 00:06:03.030
They sold them all.

16
00:06:18.629 --> 00:06:21.798
<i>Miganon.</i> The prisoners
are ready to march.

17
00:06:30.390 --> 00:06:32.643
Bring me stronger warriors.

18
00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:05.424
Thank you.

19
00:07:10.722 --> 00:07:11.557
Nawi!

20
00:07:11.640 --> 00:07:12.640
Yeah?

21
00:07:12.683 --> 00:07:15.310
Tell your mother to
see me for the dress.

22
00:07:16.103 --> 00:07:17.312
What dress?

23
00:07:18.230 --> 00:07:19.523
Your wedding dress.

24
00:07:20.023 --> 00:07:22.192
I will make you beautiful.

25
00:07:22.693 --> 00:07:23.693
Tell her.

26
00:07:24.194 --> 00:07:26.238
They have made
you another match?

27
00:07:26.321 --> 00:07:28.824
I don't know what
she's talking about.

28
00:07:31.577 --> 00:07:32.619
They are coming.

29
00:07:33.537 --> 00:07:34.538
Let's go.

30
00:07:38.792 --> 00:07:41.128
My daughter! Welcome home!

31
00:07:42.671 --> 00:07:43.505
Come here!

32
00:07:43.589 --> 00:07:45.007
Daughter! Come!

33
00:07:47.134 --> 00:07:48.510
My sister!

34
00:07:48.594 --> 00:07:50.137
My sister!

35
00:07:51.638 --> 00:07:52.848
Mother!

36
00:07:53.557 --> 00:07:55.267
I'm so happy to see you.

37
00:08:28.217 --> 00:08:29.510
But I want to see.

38
00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:33.722
The king does not allow us
to look upon the Agojie.

39
00:09:10.217 --> 00:09:11.426
Nanisca.

40
00:09:12.469 --> 00:09:14.137
It is a victory.

41
00:09:15.055 --> 00:09:16.974
They are here for you.

42
00:09:17.474 --> 00:09:19.852
They do not know
an evil is coming.

43
00:09:21.603 --> 00:09:23.564
They know you will protect them.

44
00:09:29.278 --> 00:09:31.113
I wish to speak to the king.

45
00:09:31.196 --> 00:09:32.614
He's only seeing wives today.

46
00:09:32.698 --> 00:09:34.449
Tell him. I will wait.

47
00:09:35.701 --> 00:09:38.871
The Agojie drink from the skulls
of the men they have killed.

48
00:09:38.954 --> 00:09:39.788
No.

49
00:09:39.872 --> 00:09:45.127
They cut off their heads and melt off
their skin in boiling hot cauldrons.

50
00:09:45.210 --> 00:09:46.253
Sister!

51
00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:48.130
- Sister!
- Nawi.

52
00:09:48.755 --> 00:09:50.048
We have a visitor.

53
00:09:50.132 --> 00:09:52.176
It's a rich man from Cana.

54
00:09:52.259 --> 00:09:53.468
Come.

55
00:09:54.011 --> 00:09:55.179
Come!

56
00:09:56.305 --> 00:09:58.557
Maybe he is handsome.

57
00:10:10.527 --> 00:10:13.739
I own three fields
of palm trees.

58
00:10:14.239 --> 00:10:15.407
You will work.

59
00:10:18.911 --> 00:10:21.288
You do not talk to your husband?

60
00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:28.295
In my house. you
will learn to obey.

61
00:10:31.006 --> 00:10:32.007
Nawi!

62
00:10:33.675 --> 00:10:35.427
Forgive my daughter.

63
00:10:38.263 --> 00:10:39.848
The whispers were right.

64
00:10:40.390 --> 00:10:41.391
This...

65
00:10:42.309 --> 00:10:43.644
girl is worthless.

66
00:10:45.479 --> 00:10:47.105
Master Abade.

67
00:10:54.613 --> 00:10:55.948
Come!

68
00:11:01.119 --> 00:11:04.122
I wish to give my
daughter to the king.

69
00:11:15.425 --> 00:11:16.969
No husband will have her.

70
00:11:17.052 --> 00:11:19.221
I will not marry an
old man who beats me!

71
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:21.765
Go to war. then.

72
00:11:22.307 --> 00:11:25.352
You will understand
what pain is.

73
00:11:29.356 --> 00:11:30.566
Enter.

74
00:11:41.201 --> 00:11:43.745
In the palace. you do
not have to look away.

75
00:11:46.206 --> 00:11:47.207
Come.

76
00:11:59.219 --> 00:12:00.596
Close your mouth.

77
00:12:00.679 --> 00:12:01.930
You look like a fish.

78
00:12:16.153 --> 00:12:17.362
What's in there?

79
00:12:17.446 --> 00:12:18.822
Indigo dye.

80
00:12:21.867 --> 00:12:23.493
What did you think it was?

81
00:12:24.745 --> 00:12:25.871
Heads.

82
00:12:26.788 --> 00:12:27.831
No.

83
00:12:29.499 --> 00:12:30.834
Those are the heads.

84
00:12:31.793 --> 00:12:33.712
Some of the men who
raided our village.

85
00:12:34.713 --> 00:12:37.132
The rest will be sold in Ouidah.

86
00:12:39.510 --> 00:12:43.222
No men but the eunuchs are
allowed in the palace after dark.

87
00:12:43.305 --> 00:12:46.600
Beyond this wall. this
is a palace of women.

88
00:12:56.902 --> 00:12:57.903
Come.

89
00:13:28.851 --> 00:13:29.893
Hey.

90
00:13:33.438 --> 00:13:34.898
Go and bathe yourselves.

91
00:14:18.609 --> 00:14:21.278
Oyo! Can you see this?

92
00:14:21.778 --> 00:14:25.073
Your comrades murdered.

93
00:14:26.575 --> 00:14:27.868
By women.

94
00:14:30.996 --> 00:14:35.918
The Dahomey grow too bold
under their new king.

95
00:14:39.338 --> 00:14:40.338
My loves.

96
00:14:41.673 --> 00:14:42.758
My loves.

97
00:14:44.301 --> 00:14:45.385
My love.

98
00:14:46.720 --> 00:14:47.846
My love.

99
00:14:51.099 --> 00:14:53.101
Nanisca. come with me.

100
00:15:04.947 --> 00:15:06.907
Why does he always favor her?

101
00:15:07.533 --> 00:15:10.994
She comes here filthy.
shows no respect.

102
00:15:11.662 --> 00:15:13.830
She fought for him
during the coup.

103
00:15:14.414 --> 00:15:15.541
Put him on the throne.

104
00:15:16.166 --> 00:15:17.584
What did you do?

105
00:15:18.210 --> 00:15:20.504
Locked yourself in a cupboard.

106
00:15:26.510 --> 00:15:28.428
The Oyo have entered our land.

107
00:15:30.347 --> 00:15:32.307
They have broken the peace.

108
00:15:33.559 --> 00:15:35.394
When they come
for the tribute...

109
00:15:36.353 --> 00:15:37.563
we will not pay it.

110
00:15:39.690 --> 00:15:41.108
But that would mean war.

111
00:15:41.191 --> 00:15:44.069
<i>Migan.</i> we have been under the foot
of the Oyo since my father's time.

112
00:15:44.152 --> 00:15:45.152
Are you not tired?

113
00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:49.491
Because we fear their might.

114
00:15:51.118 --> 00:15:52.369
Because of fear.

115
00:15:53.328 --> 00:15:56.832
My king. they are a
nation twice our size.

116
00:15:56.915 --> 00:15:58.959
with horses and more muskets.

117
00:15:59.042 --> 00:16:02.087
We need time to plan
and prepare our armies.

118
00:16:02.171 --> 00:16:03.755
The Agojie are ready.

119
00:16:03.839 --> 00:16:06.383
How many did you lose
in this last battle?

120
00:16:06.466 --> 00:16:07.926
Against the lowly Mahi?

121
00:16:10.095 --> 00:16:10.971
My king.

122
00:16:11.054 --> 00:16:13.223
I hear whispers
of a new general.

123
00:16:13.724 --> 00:16:17.603
This last attack was
sword-rattling. Nothing more.

124
00:16:17.686 --> 00:16:19.104
I agree.

125
00:16:19.188 --> 00:16:22.482
Dahomey has prospered in
the peace. And the Oyo too.

126
00:16:22.566 --> 00:16:25.777
The slave trade is
the reason we prosper.

127
00:16:25.861 --> 00:16:27.529
But at what price?

128
00:16:27.613 --> 00:16:31.825
It is a poison slowly killing
us. And the Europeans know this.

129
00:16:32.242 --> 00:16:34.745
They come to our land
for their human cargo.

130
00:16:34.828 --> 00:16:37.956
They've come to trade. We
sell them what they want.

131
00:16:38.040 --> 00:16:40.292
But why do we sell our captives?

132
00:16:40.375 --> 00:16:41.710
For weapons?

133
00:16:42.211 --> 00:16:44.630
To capture more people
to sell for more weapons?

134
00:16:44.713 --> 00:16:48.091
It is a dark circle with no end.

135
00:16:48.175 --> 00:16:49.885
This is not the way.

136
00:16:49.968 --> 00:16:53.472
The spirits have
spoken. Ifá seeks light.

137
00:16:55.224 --> 00:16:57.392
So. what do you
suggest. Nanisca?

138
00:16:57.476 --> 00:16:59.728
We have other things to sell.

139
00:17:00.187 --> 00:17:01.605
Gold. Palm oil.

140
00:17:01.688 --> 00:17:02.981
We can double our harvest.

141
00:17:03.065 --> 00:17:05.358
She wants to make us
a nation of peasants.

142
00:17:05.442 --> 00:17:07.402
I want Dahomey to survive.

143
00:17:10.781 --> 00:17:12.824
The gods have brought
us a new king.

144
00:17:13.367 --> 00:17:15.077
A king to be feared.

145
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:16.912
No one fears a farmer.

146
00:17:17.538 --> 00:17:20.499
We have already started
to gather the tribute.

147
00:17:20.958 --> 00:17:24.002
Perhaps we pay. to buy us time.

148
00:17:27.964 --> 00:17:29.216
I promise...

149
00:17:31.051 --> 00:17:32.469
this will be our last.

150
00:17:34.012 --> 00:17:36.682
As for the palm oil. Nanisca.

151
00:17:37.683 --> 00:17:38.684
show me.

152
00:17:39.268 --> 00:17:42.187
Show me how much you can
produce and we will see.

153
00:17:53.699 --> 00:17:55.993
You speak in secret to the king.

154
00:17:56.076 --> 00:17:57.828
You seek to cut me out.

155
00:17:57.911 --> 00:18:02.082
If the king respects me. it
is because I have earned it.

156
00:18:11.258 --> 00:18:13.010
I am Amenza.

157
00:18:13.093 --> 00:18:15.554
You come to the palace of Ghezo.

158
00:18:16.263 --> 00:18:18.765
the ninth monarch of
the Dahomey people.

159
00:18:19.433 --> 00:18:22.060
descendants of the
leopard. Agasu.

160
00:18:22.603 --> 00:18:27.065
beloved of the twin gods.
Mawu and her brother. Leesa.

161
00:18:28.108 --> 00:18:31.236
You are called to
join the King's Guard.

162
00:18:37.993 --> 00:18:39.328
We fight.

163
00:18:40.204 --> 00:18:41.830
or we die.

164
00:18:45.250 --> 00:18:47.586
We fight for Dahomey...

165
00:18:49.087 --> 00:18:50.756
for our sisters...

166
00:18:51.632 --> 00:18:53.509
for our great king.

167
00:18:54.092 --> 00:18:56.220
You will be revered.

168
00:18:57.304 --> 00:18:59.556
You will be paid for your work.

169
00:19:00.265 --> 00:19:02.351
Your opinions will be heard.

170
00:19:03.101 --> 00:19:08.440
No tribe or kingdom in all of
Africa shares this privilege.

171
00:19:09.566 --> 00:19:11.109
For this honor...

172
00:19:11.193 --> 00:19:14.446
we live out our lives
in these palace walls.

173
00:19:17.241 --> 00:19:19.493
We take no husband.

174
00:19:20.244 --> 00:19:22.120
We will bear no children.

175
00:19:23.247 --> 00:19:24.623
Mahi women.

176
00:19:24.706 --> 00:19:28.168
no harm will come to you
for the sins of your men.

177
00:19:28.252 --> 00:19:31.588
I offer you and our
people a choice.

178
00:19:33.507 --> 00:19:36.593
Any woman who does
not wish to stay...

179
00:19:38.887 --> 00:19:39.930
may leave.

180
00:20:13.255 --> 00:20:16.091
Do not touch another
warrior's weapon.

181
00:20:16.967 --> 00:20:18.719
Especially that one.

182
00:20:19.428 --> 00:20:20.428
It is cursed.

183
00:20:21.722 --> 00:20:24.892
Esi couldn't hit an
elephant in a stampede.

184
00:20:24.975 --> 00:20:27.644
Turn your back and see
how true my aim is.

185
00:20:27.728 --> 00:20:29.104
Me?

186
00:20:38.947 --> 00:20:43.285
Spent all my liberties walking the river
till I found the perfect whetstone.

187
00:20:43.368 --> 00:20:46.330
Shaped smooth by the waterfall.

188
00:20:46.413 --> 00:20:47.956
Sharpens to a thorn.

189
00:20:50.792 --> 00:20:53.587
Pop out their eyeballs.
fight is over.

190
00:20:55.547 --> 00:20:58.800
They are also useful in
keeping the trainees in line.

191
00:20:59.510 --> 00:21:00.969
Why have you not bathed?

192
00:21:01.053 --> 00:21:02.638
You are going to
bring the buzzards.

193
00:21:03.138 --> 00:21:05.390
I let the others go before me.

194
00:21:06.183 --> 00:21:08.560
The first rule of training:

195
00:21:08.644 --> 00:21:11.021
Always obey Izogie.

196
00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:16.985
I am Izogie.

197
00:21:42.177 --> 00:21:43.387
I'm sorry.

198
00:21:44.429 --> 00:21:46.056
You may stay.

199
00:21:48.058 --> 00:21:49.852
You are one of the
captives we freed?

200
00:21:49.935 --> 00:21:50.769
No.

201
00:21:50.853 --> 00:21:52.855
My father brought me.

202
00:21:52.938 --> 00:21:54.690
As a gift to the king.

203
00:21:54.773 --> 00:21:56.358
Is your father rich?

204
00:21:56.775 --> 00:21:58.151
He must be.

205
00:21:59.069 --> 00:22:01.655
Otherwise he would have
sold you to a rich husband.

206
00:22:01.738 --> 00:22:02.990
He tried.

207
00:22:03.949 --> 00:22:05.909
I do not want a husband.

208
00:22:06.660 --> 00:22:08.120
I want to be a soldier.

209
00:22:08.203 --> 00:22:09.454
An Agojie.

210
00:22:09.538 --> 00:22:10.372
How old are you?

211
00:22:10.455 --> 00:22:12.040
I have 19 years.

212
00:22:12.124 --> 00:22:13.750
You look like a child.

213
00:22:13.834 --> 00:22:15.127
I work hard.

214
00:22:15.627 --> 00:22:17.171
Harder than anyone.

215
00:22:17.254 --> 00:22:20.716
Many obstinate daughters
are dumped at the palace.

216
00:22:20.799 --> 00:22:22.593
They usually fail.

217
00:22:24.261 --> 00:22:28.974
All our lives they tell us
stories about the Agojie.

218
00:22:29.516 --> 00:22:30.976
That you have magic.

219
00:22:31.852 --> 00:22:34.229
You look like a regular
old woman to me.

220
00:22:37.900 --> 00:22:41.278
Fighting is not magic.

221
00:22:42.321 --> 00:22:43.739
It is skill.

222
00:22:44.281 --> 00:22:46.200
We will see if you have any.

223
00:23:00.756 --> 00:23:02.508
I am not a soldier.

224
00:23:04.009 --> 00:23:05.552
Then why did you stay?

225
00:23:06.553 --> 00:23:08.514
I have nowhere else to go.

226
00:23:11.058 --> 00:23:12.392
You are Mahi.

227
00:23:13.352 --> 00:23:14.686
Why did you stay?

228
00:23:15.354 --> 00:23:17.397
Here I will be the hunter.

229
00:23:17.481 --> 00:23:18.899
not prey.

230
00:23:38.460 --> 00:23:41.505
Today you are receiving
your first weapon.

231
00:23:55.477 --> 00:23:56.520
Not good.

232
00:24:00.566 --> 00:24:01.608
Good.

233
00:24:06.238 --> 00:24:07.406
Again.

234
00:24:08.824 --> 00:24:10.409
A rope is not a weapon.

235
00:24:12.703 --> 00:24:14.788
You wish for a different weapon?

236
00:24:15.706 --> 00:24:16.706
Stand up.

237
00:24:20.043 --> 00:24:22.588
Go. Attack the
soldier. Take his head.

238
00:24:28.010 --> 00:24:30.345
- I apologize.
- Do not apologize. Do it.

239
00:25:00.834 --> 00:25:02.211
I'd work on that rope.

240
00:25:09.343 --> 00:25:10.427
Hey.

241
00:25:10.511 --> 00:25:11.678
Tsetse.

242
00:25:12.846 --> 00:25:13.889
Who's Tsetse?

243
00:25:13.972 --> 00:25:16.183
You. Little fly.

244
00:25:16.266 --> 00:25:18.810
Buzzing around full speed.

245
00:25:19.394 --> 00:25:21.396
But you don't know
where you are going.

246
00:25:21.480 --> 00:25:23.357
We need smart warriors.

247
00:25:23.440 --> 00:25:24.858
The dumb ones die quickly.

248
00:25:24.942 --> 00:25:26.068
I'm not dumb.

249
00:25:26.151 --> 00:25:27.653
Then show me.

250
00:25:27.736 --> 00:25:29.821
You have to train different.

251
00:25:29.905 --> 00:25:32.241
The drills are a game.

252
00:25:32.324 --> 00:25:35.077
It is play. like when
you were a child.

253
00:25:35.160 --> 00:25:37.037
I was not allowed to play.

254
00:25:37.579 --> 00:25:39.164
I was made to work.

255
00:25:39.248 --> 00:25:41.542
Such a sad tale.

256
00:25:42.042 --> 00:25:43.168
You don't know anything.

257
00:25:49.299 --> 00:25:50.300
You know...

258
00:25:51.051 --> 00:25:53.220
when I had 14 years...

259
00:25:54.054 --> 00:25:57.182
my mother put a sign out
to sell my virginity.

260
00:25:58.600 --> 00:26:02.437
The first man came and
I cried for my mother.

261
00:26:02.521 --> 00:26:04.022
but she didn't come.

262
00:26:04.106 --> 00:26:07.693
The second man came and
complained of my tears.

263
00:26:07.776 --> 00:26:08.902
so she beat me.

264
00:26:09.486 --> 00:26:10.988
The third man came.

265
00:26:11.530 --> 00:26:13.365
and I burned him with an ember.

266
00:26:18.453 --> 00:26:20.122
Your family was cruel.

267
00:26:20.747 --> 00:26:21.915
As was my mother.

268
00:26:23.292 --> 00:26:25.043
It is enough to make you cry.

269
00:26:26.962 --> 00:26:29.548
But it is better to laugh. Yes?

270
00:26:31.758 --> 00:26:33.510
You have a new family now.

271
00:26:39.725 --> 00:26:40.767
Trainees.

272
00:26:40.851 --> 00:26:43.437
We will prepare you
for the final test.

273
00:26:43.520 --> 00:26:46.315
You will perform your battle
skills before the king.

274
00:26:47.983 --> 00:26:51.570
<i>Those who pass the test
will become Agojie.</i>

275
00:26:52.196 --> 00:26:55.199
<i>And those who fail
will leave the palace.</i>

276
00:26:55.282 --> 00:26:56.992
<i>never to return.</i>

277
00:27:01.288 --> 00:27:02.372
Look at you.

278
00:27:02.873 --> 00:27:04.333
The Oyo will catch you.

279
00:27:04.416 --> 00:27:06.335
Hang you by your feet
and cut your throat.

280
00:27:07.794 --> 00:27:09.463
Use your feet and walk.

281
00:27:29.024 --> 00:27:31.360
Get up. You are
just waiting to die.

282
00:27:35.739 --> 00:27:37.449
Are we training to cook?

283
00:27:38.325 --> 00:27:41.161
You are cutting a
body. not a yam.

284
00:27:42.120 --> 00:27:43.455
Swing with purpose!

285
00:27:52.089 --> 00:27:53.089
Ready.

286
00:27:53.799 --> 00:27:54.799
Fire!

287
00:28:01.056 --> 00:28:02.140
Good. Ode.

288
00:28:03.183 --> 00:28:05.269
Nawi. you move like a sloth.

289
00:28:54.318 --> 00:28:55.736
- Agojie!
- Wu Suu!

290
00:28:56.820 --> 00:28:58.280
- Agojie!
- Wu Suu!

291
00:28:59.406 --> 00:29:00.824
- Agojie!
- Wu Suu!

292
00:29:08.665 --> 00:29:09.665
Fumbe.

293
00:29:10.334 --> 00:29:12.294
Show me how to tie the rope.

294
00:29:13.170 --> 00:29:14.421
Never.

295
00:29:14.505 --> 00:29:17.132
It is the only thing I
can do better than you.

296
00:29:17.925 --> 00:29:19.718
Ode. This one.

297
00:29:22.804 --> 00:29:24.806
But did you see Izogie?

298
00:29:25.849 --> 00:29:27.226
With the dagger here.

299
00:29:27.309 --> 00:29:30.270
She's standing there.
not moving. not in pain.

300
00:29:32.147 --> 00:29:34.733
- I'm going to be like her.
- Yes. my friend.

301
00:29:34.816 --> 00:29:36.235
As strong as her.

302
00:29:36.652 --> 00:29:38.654
You try to stab me.
I'll stab you back.

303
00:29:40.739 --> 00:29:42.074
Backswing.

304
00:29:57.673 --> 00:29:59.967
Which of you
designed this trick?

305
00:30:05.430 --> 00:30:06.765
Then you will all be punished.

306
00:30:06.849 --> 00:30:07.683
I did it.

307
00:30:07.766 --> 00:30:08.767
We all did it.

308
00:30:08.851 --> 00:30:09.851
No.

309
00:30:10.978 --> 00:30:12.187
It was me.

310
00:30:12.896 --> 00:30:13.939
I apologize.

311
00:30:14.565 --> 00:30:16.066
Once again.

312
00:30:18.110 --> 00:30:19.528
Go back to the barracks.

313
00:30:25.033 --> 00:30:28.537
How do you make this explosion?

314
00:30:29.913 --> 00:30:32.457
You do not need guns
to use gunpowder.

315
00:30:32.541 --> 00:30:34.168
You just need a spark.

316
00:30:35.919 --> 00:30:37.379
You like the guns?

317
00:30:38.755 --> 00:30:41.425
Do you enjoy practicing with
the men in the infantry?

318
00:30:41.925 --> 00:30:43.135
I see you flirting.

319
00:30:44.386 --> 00:30:46.513
- This is not allowed?
- You know it is not.

320
00:30:46.597 --> 00:30:47.723
Why not?

321
00:30:48.599 --> 00:30:51.185
The men who are soldiers
have wives and children.

322
00:30:51.268 --> 00:30:52.769
But the Agojie cannot.

323
00:30:53.395 --> 00:30:54.605
How is that fair?

324
00:30:54.688 --> 00:30:58.233
Were you this arrogant with your
family? No wonder they gave you away.

325
00:30:58.317 --> 00:31:00.194
It is you who is arrogant.

326
00:31:01.862 --> 00:31:03.405
I am a general.

327
00:31:04.198 --> 00:31:05.365
I have earned it.

328
00:31:05.449 --> 00:31:07.159
You have earned nothing.

329
00:31:07.242 --> 00:31:09.119
I should put you out.

330
00:31:09.203 --> 00:31:12.331
I have watched soldiers die because
they did not have discipline.

331
00:31:12.414 --> 00:31:14.333
Their easy life did
not prepare them...

332
00:31:14.416 --> 00:31:17.461
- I did not have an easy life.
- For this life here as an Agojie.

333
00:31:20.172 --> 00:31:22.424
I did not have an easy life.

334
00:31:22.883 --> 00:31:23.926
Please.

335
00:31:24.009 --> 00:31:27.804
I want to be here with the others.
I want to fight for my king.

336
00:31:30.349 --> 00:31:31.350
Please.

337
00:31:32.809 --> 00:31:33.936
Your tears...

338
00:31:34.811 --> 00:31:36.230
mean nothing.

339
00:31:38.565 --> 00:31:41.068
To be a warrior. you
must kill your tears.

340
00:31:49.243 --> 00:31:50.244
Go.

341
00:32:01.380 --> 00:32:02.381
Go.

342
00:32:10.305 --> 00:32:11.305
Hey.

343
00:32:12.766 --> 00:32:14.268
You are a Mahi prisoner.

344
00:32:14.351 --> 00:32:16.228
That is all you will ever be.

345
00:32:16.311 --> 00:32:17.688
What did you say?

346
00:32:18.772 --> 00:32:20.899
- She killed our people.
- You killed mine.

347
00:32:20.983 --> 00:32:23.694
Me. I also came here a captive.

348
00:32:24.403 --> 00:32:26.780
Do you think yourself
better than me?

349
00:32:27.239 --> 00:32:28.448
No. <i>Ajahi.</i>

350
00:32:28.532 --> 00:32:31.910
If you make it through the
final test. you are one of us.

351
00:32:33.161 --> 00:32:34.955
No matter where you come from.

352
00:32:47.301 --> 00:32:48.886
Hey. Tsetse.

353
00:32:48.969 --> 00:32:50.262
Eat up.

354
00:32:50.345 --> 00:32:51.930
Nanisca favors the strong.

355
00:32:54.433 --> 00:32:55.976
What is the first
rule of training?

356
00:33:01.481 --> 00:33:03.358
Always obey Izogie.

357
00:33:07.988 --> 00:33:09.072
Come with me.

358
00:33:13.202 --> 00:33:14.203
Drink.

359
00:33:15.579 --> 00:33:16.830
What is it?

360
00:33:17.247 --> 00:33:20.125
The only thing the white
men bring worth having.

361
00:33:20.209 --> 00:33:22.044
They call it "whiskey."

362
00:33:24.379 --> 00:33:25.422
There.

363
00:33:25.506 --> 00:33:28.175
We finally found a
way to quiet Tse.

364
00:33:29.051 --> 00:33:32.012
You know your tongue will get
you kicked back to your village.

365
00:33:32.095 --> 00:33:34.014
Why do you challenge
the <i>Miganon?</i>

366
00:33:34.848 --> 00:33:37.059
If I'm quiet. she won't see me.

367
00:33:37.476 --> 00:33:39.770
Do you think she has
time to think about you?

368
00:33:40.562 --> 00:33:43.482
She is thinking about the world.

369
00:33:43.565 --> 00:33:46.026
You know she may one
day be the <i>Kpojito.</i>

370
00:33:46.109 --> 00:33:47.319
The Woman King?

371
00:33:48.612 --> 00:33:51.240
But we have not had
one in so many years.

372
00:33:51.323 --> 00:33:53.450
His brother did not honor it.

373
00:33:53.534 --> 00:33:57.120
but King Ghezo
believes in tradition.

374
00:33:57.204 --> 00:34:00.707
In the twin gods.
Mawu and Leesa.

375
00:34:00.791 --> 00:34:02.584
Woman and man.

376
00:34:03.043 --> 00:34:04.169
Equal.

377
00:34:04.920 --> 00:34:07.089
Ghezo will name a Woman King.

378
00:34:07.172 --> 00:34:09.466
For the gods. And the people.

379
00:34:10.467 --> 00:34:12.678
But is that what
the <i>Miganon </i>wants?

380
00:34:12.761 --> 00:34:14.054
I cannot say.

381
00:34:15.013 --> 00:34:18.266
But in the palace.
she is a legend.

382
00:34:18.891 --> 00:34:21.018
Captured as a young soldier.

383
00:34:21.103 --> 00:34:22.771
Given up for dead.

384
00:34:23.230 --> 00:34:24.982
But she returned.

385
00:34:25.524 --> 00:34:29.862
with the Oyo bastards'
<i>kofes</i> hanging by her belt.

386
00:34:55.137 --> 00:34:57.347
You know I hate that drink.

387
00:34:57.848 --> 00:35:00.058
The king drinks
anything I give him.

388
00:35:00.142 --> 00:35:01.560
The king is young.

389
00:35:01.643 --> 00:35:04.521
He brings that silly
wife to the council.

390
00:35:05.272 --> 00:35:06.398
Shante.

391
00:35:08.317 --> 00:35:10.027
She is ambitious.

392
00:35:20.370 --> 00:35:22.664
Tell me the dream. Nani.

393
00:35:25.042 --> 00:35:29.421
It dispels its magic
if you say the words.

394
00:35:33.342 --> 00:35:35.385
I am in the jungle.

395
00:35:38.847 --> 00:35:42.559
Something is out
there. in the darkness.

396
00:35:45.062 --> 00:35:46.313
A beast.

397
00:35:46.396 --> 00:35:47.564
Angry.

398
00:35:52.945 --> 00:35:55.906
I can smell its sweat. its fear.

399
00:35:56.615 --> 00:35:58.825
What does the beast look like?

400
00:35:59.701 --> 00:36:01.078
I don't know.

401
00:36:01.954 --> 00:36:03.705
That is when I wake.

402
00:36:06.166 --> 00:36:08.043
The dream is a warning. no?

403
00:36:09.419 --> 00:36:11.463
We must ask Legba.

404
00:36:11.547 --> 00:36:14.216
Oh. no. Not the nuts.

405
00:36:14.800 --> 00:36:16.718
Do not call them "nuts."

406
00:36:18.053 --> 00:36:19.763
They are sacred.

407
00:36:28.522 --> 00:36:30.649
You have enemies gathering.

408
00:36:31.400 --> 00:36:33.110
You must do better than that.

409
00:36:36.905 --> 00:36:38.448
I see fire.

410
00:36:40.117 --> 00:36:44.371
Something or someone
from your past.

411
00:36:45.414 --> 00:36:47.165
This is nonsense.

412
00:36:47.249 --> 00:36:50.043
And your medicine too.
I am not even tired.

413
00:36:50.127 --> 00:36:51.587
Go to the altar.

414
00:36:52.671 --> 00:36:54.840
Leave gifts for the dead.

415
00:36:57.551 --> 00:36:58.802
Do it.

416
00:37:00.262 --> 00:37:04.349
If you do not respect Ifá.
respect your own dream.

417
00:39:28.952 --> 00:39:31.788
I am General Oba Ade...

418
00:39:37.586 --> 00:39:40.589
the esteemed regard
of the King of Oyo.

419
00:39:42.382 --> 00:39:46.178
Gifts for the Oyo
Kingdom. as is tradition.

420
00:39:48.222 --> 00:39:49.222
Nanisca.

421
00:39:57.439 --> 00:39:58.774
This is less than ever before.

422
00:39:59.316 --> 00:40:00.984
Did you think we would not see?

423
00:40:01.068 --> 00:40:04.154
Did you think we would not see your
hand in the raid of our village?

424
00:40:07.199 --> 00:40:11.745
To make up for your shortcomings. I
will accept an addition to the tribute.

425
00:40:11.828 --> 00:40:13.747
Forty Agojie.

426
00:40:15.165 --> 00:40:16.250
Not too old.

427
00:40:20.337 --> 00:40:21.505
And if I refuse?

428
00:40:21.588 --> 00:40:24.258
Then you may no longer use the
port in Ouidah for your trade.

429
00:40:24.341 --> 00:40:26.218
The port belongs to Dahomey.

430
00:40:26.301 --> 00:40:28.929
We have taken control.
It belongs to us now.

431
00:40:33.892 --> 00:40:36.687
I'm so surprised you brought
your horses here to plateau.

432
00:40:37.229 --> 00:40:40.274
If they are bitten by the flies.
they may get the sleeping sickness.

433
00:40:42.734 --> 00:40:46.780
Sometimes a mouse can
take down an elephant.

434
00:40:46.864 --> 00:40:48.991
Do you threaten
the Oyo. usurper?

435
00:40:49.074 --> 00:40:50.367
You will respect the king!

436
00:40:53.662 --> 00:40:54.830
<i>Migan.</i>

437
00:40:54.913 --> 00:40:57.499
This new general
seeks to bait us.

438
00:40:57.583 --> 00:40:59.251
We won't jump at
his foolishness.

439
00:40:59.334 --> 00:41:00.627
Let us talk.

440
00:41:16.393 --> 00:41:17.978
Twenty Agojie.

441
00:41:18.061 --> 00:41:20.105
Of our choosing.

442
00:41:20.772 --> 00:41:23.150
We will march them to
Ouidah and surrender them.

443
00:41:23.609 --> 00:41:26.278
And the port remains
open for our trade.

444
00:41:27.613 --> 00:41:31.158
I will leave Boma to enjoy the
feast that you have prepared.

445
00:41:32.075 --> 00:41:34.953
In Ouidah. I will be waiting.

446
00:41:36.288 --> 00:41:37.288
Oba.

447
00:43:03.500 --> 00:43:04.501
Nanisca.

448
00:43:07.754 --> 00:43:09.131
What happened?

449
00:43:09.673 --> 00:43:11.884
Your nuts were finally right.

450
00:43:44.249 --> 00:43:45.667
I can't believe it.

451
00:43:46.376 --> 00:43:47.753
I'm really here.

452
00:43:48.921 --> 00:43:50.214
It is a savage place.

453
00:43:51.798 --> 00:43:53.967
I'm afraid you will not
find it to your liking

454
00:43:54.051 --> 00:43:56.094
after the comforts
of your upbringing.

455
00:43:56.720 --> 00:43:58.972
I can say the same
for your ship.

456
00:44:01.225 --> 00:44:04.144
Slave ships are the only kind
that come to these shores.

457
00:44:05.020 --> 00:44:07.814
And I intend to run
it as my father.

458
00:44:07.898 --> 00:44:12.319
Your father runs a print
shop. That is all you know.

459
00:44:14.279 --> 00:44:15.279
Come.

460
00:44:16.073 --> 00:44:17.658
Let's see the city.

461
00:45:05.414 --> 00:45:06.456
Agojie.

462
00:45:06.540 --> 00:45:08.208
Agojie's here.

463
00:45:24.474 --> 00:45:26.810
- Are they...?
- The Dahomey Amazons.

464
00:45:27.394 --> 00:45:28.687
Virgin soldiers.

465
00:45:29.229 --> 00:45:31.231
Bloodiest bitches in Africa.

466
00:45:43.160 --> 00:45:45.495
We bring tribute
from King Ghezo.

467
00:45:46.622 --> 00:45:52.294
Dahomey has no soldiers man enough.
They have to use their women.

468
00:45:53.795 --> 00:45:55.547
It is against the gods!

469
00:45:57.299 --> 00:45:59.968
My men will find
plenty of use for them.

470
00:46:00.052 --> 00:46:01.303
You're mistaken.

471
00:46:02.346 --> 00:46:04.598
These soldiers are
not your tribute.

472
00:46:04.681 --> 00:46:06.517
This is your tribute.

473
00:46:08.393 --> 00:46:10.437
Let it be known to all!

474
00:46:12.105 --> 00:46:14.733
The great and mighty
King Ghezo fears no one!

475
00:46:26.286 --> 00:46:28.747
- Oyo!
- Oyo!

476
00:47:07.911 --> 00:47:08.912
Lift the gate!

477
00:47:23.218 --> 00:47:24.845
<i>Miganon!</i>

478
00:47:25.512 --> 00:47:26.847
Go!

479
00:47:31.685 --> 00:47:32.685
Go!

480
00:47:33.770 --> 00:47:34.770
Go!

481
00:48:17.606 --> 00:48:18.690
Push off.

482
00:48:31.036 --> 00:48:34.623
Why did you not follow the plan?
You were to go to the boats.

483
00:48:34.706 --> 00:48:36.375
The soldiers were coming.

484
00:48:36.458 --> 00:48:38.877
- If I did not come back as I did...
- So you are the hero?

485
00:48:38.961 --> 00:48:40.796
You can act on your
own. ignoring orders?

486
00:48:42.005 --> 00:48:44.424
- You would not have escaped.
- Nawi.

487
00:48:48.804 --> 00:48:52.015
It is you who faced capture
by disobeying my orders.

488
00:48:56.311 --> 00:48:58.146
We are Agojie.

489
00:48:58.939 --> 00:49:00.190
We do not act alone.

490
00:49:00.899 --> 00:49:04.194
We move together with one
purpose. Alone you are weak.

491
00:49:04.778 --> 00:49:06.738
Alone you are killed or worse.

492
00:49:08.282 --> 00:49:10.242
Now you have seen
the barracoons.

493
00:49:11.451 --> 00:49:13.745
A captured Agojie is a slave.

494
00:49:14.997 --> 00:49:17.916
Used by men. Left to rot.

495
00:49:21.336 --> 00:49:22.796
It is better to die.

496
00:49:24.006 --> 00:49:25.340
Cut your own throat.

497
00:49:33.015 --> 00:49:35.934
I will never question you
in front of the others.

498
00:49:36.018 --> 00:49:38.520
but it is you who did
not follow the plan.

499
00:49:38.604 --> 00:49:41.481
I only ever had
one plan. Amenza.

500
00:49:41.982 --> 00:49:44.359
- To take his head.
- Nanisca. I...

501
00:50:10.177 --> 00:50:11.177
Nanisca.

502
00:50:12.221 --> 00:50:13.305
Come in.

503
00:50:18.685 --> 00:50:20.479
I hear you have had a victory.

504
00:50:24.066 --> 00:50:29.071
Nanisca. I think we have started on a
wrong foot. I wish to be your friend.

505
00:50:29.905 --> 00:50:32.658
I can help you. I
have the king's ear.

506
00:50:32.741 --> 00:50:36.703
We should work together to serve our king
to ensure he grows only more powerful.

507
00:50:36.787 --> 00:50:39.248
It is you who wants
to be powerful.

508
00:50:40.040 --> 00:50:43.669
To stay safe and rich
in your fine palace.

509
00:50:46.088 --> 00:50:50.884
Too much change can be dangerous. I
have said this much to my husband.

510
00:50:52.052 --> 00:50:55.097
Then we will soon understand
who truly has his ear.

511
00:51:12.489 --> 00:51:17.411
This field alone produces
thousands of barrels of palm oil.

512
00:51:17.494 --> 00:51:22.499
If we harvest many fields each year. we
will have a continuous supply to trade.

513
00:51:24.710 --> 00:51:26.920
I never saw a path
before. Nanisca.

514
00:51:28.714 --> 00:51:31.466
But look at this. Now I do.

515
00:51:32.217 --> 00:51:34.386
Vision is seeing
what others do not.

516
00:51:35.846 --> 00:51:37.639
But now we have declared war.

517
00:51:38.265 --> 00:51:42.144
We will conquer the Oyo.
and we will expand our land.

518
00:51:43.395 --> 00:51:46.398
Nanisca. we will be the
greatest empire in Africa.

519
00:51:46.481 --> 00:51:47.941
Yes. my king.

520
00:51:48.025 --> 00:51:51.445
But let us not be an empire
who sells its people.

521
00:51:52.196 --> 00:51:56.450
- Let us be an empire who loves its people.
- My brother sold our own.

522
00:51:58.202 --> 00:51:59.453
I will never do that.

523
00:51:59.536 --> 00:52:03.123
Even if they are not Dahomey.
they are still our people.

524
00:52:04.750 --> 00:52:07.336
The white man has
brought immorality here.

525
00:52:07.419 --> 00:52:11.423
They will not stop until the whole
of Africa is theirs to enslave.

526
00:52:12.508 --> 00:52:13.508
Go.

527
00:52:18.680 --> 00:52:21.141
The English Navy now
patrols the waters.

528
00:52:22.434 --> 00:52:24.478
attacks and removes our cargo.

529
00:52:24.561 --> 00:52:27.314
Your tribal warfare
is none of my concern.

530
00:52:27.397 --> 00:52:29.608
And yours with Dahomey
is none of ours.

531
00:52:29.691 --> 00:52:31.818
It will be over soon enough.

532
00:52:33.028 --> 00:52:36.114
The Mahi. the Igbo.
they are with us.

533
00:52:36.865 --> 00:52:40.911
By the full moon. we will march on
their city. and we will take it.

534
00:52:40.994 --> 00:52:45.082
Ouidah is open for business.
You will have your cargo.

535
00:52:59.012 --> 00:53:00.681
You wish to see Dahomey?

536
00:53:01.807 --> 00:53:05.602
Then we must go now.
Before it is no more.

537
00:54:36.109 --> 00:54:37.109
Santo!

538
00:54:39.196 --> 00:54:40.697
This isn't funny!

539
00:54:48.455 --> 00:54:50.165
You've got my clothes.

540
00:54:50.249 --> 00:54:52.709
Go back to Ouidah. slaver.

541
00:54:52.793 --> 00:54:54.795
Naked like the people you sell.

542
00:54:55.629 --> 00:54:56.839
I am not a slaver.

543
00:54:57.506 --> 00:54:58.715
You understand me?

544
00:54:59.299 --> 00:55:01.093
My mother was Dahomey.

545
00:55:02.845 --> 00:55:04.805
You do not look like Dahomey.

546
00:55:05.514 --> 00:55:07.140
My father is white.

547
00:55:08.600 --> 00:55:11.520
So you are Dahomey but not.

548
00:55:12.521 --> 00:55:13.522
And white...

549
00:55:15.399 --> 00:55:16.399
but not.

550
00:55:19.278 --> 00:55:21.405
You think I could
have my pants now?

551
00:55:27.578 --> 00:55:29.121
I saw you in Ouidah.

552
00:55:30.664 --> 00:55:32.791
Why are you here in the jungle?

553
00:55:32.875 --> 00:55:34.626
I am going to Dahomey.

554
00:55:35.711 --> 00:55:38.213
The place my mother
told me so much about.

555
00:55:39.882 --> 00:55:44.761
- Perhaps I will see you there too.
- If you are allowed into the palace.

556
00:56:10.287 --> 00:56:11.580
I am Malik.

557
00:56:13.248 --> 00:56:14.248
Malik!

558
00:56:34.436 --> 00:56:37.064
I do not like this
young captain.

559
00:56:37.147 --> 00:56:39.483
Puffed up like a banty rooster.

560
00:56:39.566 --> 00:56:40.984
Finally we agree.

561
00:56:41.068 --> 00:56:42.277
Too long. Santo!

562
00:56:44.530 --> 00:56:45.739
You hide yourself!

563
00:56:49.076 --> 00:56:53.372
Your Portuguese is flawless. Your
Majesty. My father sends his regards.

564
00:56:53.956 --> 00:56:55.832
So you are now a captain?

565
00:56:55.916 --> 00:56:57.084
- <i>Sim</i>.
- Very good.

566
00:56:57.167 --> 00:56:58.293
He taught me well.

567
00:56:58.836 --> 00:57:00.796
Gifts. For you.

568
00:57:02.130 --> 00:57:03.130
Well done.

569
00:57:11.223 --> 00:57:12.516
You have my thanks.

570
00:57:16.937 --> 00:57:20.607
This is Malik. His mother was
taken from Dahomey as a captive.

571
00:57:23.777 --> 00:57:25.571
My mother was also taken.

572
00:57:26.530 --> 00:57:27.948
Sold by my brother.

573
00:57:29.283 --> 00:57:33.328
I have many men in your country searching
for her. and they will bring her back.

574
00:57:33.412 --> 00:57:34.412
It is a must.

575
00:57:35.330 --> 00:57:39.459
And if they find your mother.
they will bring her back too.

576
00:57:40.794 --> 00:57:42.254
I have just buried her.

577
00:57:43.297 --> 00:57:46.008
It was her dying wish
that I come to her home.

578
00:57:46.091 --> 00:57:48.051
the only place
she was ever free.

579
00:57:49.720 --> 00:57:50.846
This is your home.

580
00:57:51.388 --> 00:57:52.764
It is yours.

581
00:57:53.974 --> 00:57:56.226
And you came on the right day.

582
00:57:56.310 --> 00:57:59.771
Our magnificent Agojie. they
are doing their final test.

583
00:57:59.855 --> 00:58:02.024
So. please. sit.

584
00:58:02.107 --> 00:58:03.901
Go. Go on. sit. Go.

585
00:58:03.984 --> 00:58:05.611
Prepare the seats for them.

586
00:58:09.114 --> 00:58:10.114
Very good.

587
00:58:12.284 --> 00:58:13.493
Let us begin!

588
00:58:18.498 --> 00:58:19.625
Go.

589
00:58:38.268 --> 00:58:39.311
Fear not.

590
00:58:39.895 --> 00:58:40.979
Face it head-on.

591
00:58:42.105 --> 00:58:44.316
Relentlessly we will fight.

592
00:59:17.182 --> 00:59:18.225
Fumbe.

593
00:59:22.938 --> 00:59:24.648
- No. no. no.
- Come.

594
00:59:29.653 --> 00:59:32.030
Come. Come. Come.

595
01:01:04.623 --> 01:01:05.624
Come.

596
01:01:05.707 --> 01:01:08.335
Come. come. come. my
dear. Come. come. come.

597
01:01:13.924 --> 01:01:15.133
What is your name?

598
01:01:15.217 --> 01:01:16.552
I am Nawi. my king.

599
01:01:16.635 --> 01:01:17.635
Nawi.

600
01:01:18.011 --> 01:01:20.347
You are beautiful
as you are fierce.

601
01:01:21.932 --> 01:01:24.893
If she was not so skilled. I
would have made her a wife.

602
01:01:30.065 --> 01:01:31.400
To the victor!

603
01:01:35.988 --> 01:01:39.408
The gods will bless you.
The gods will keep you safe.

604
01:01:45.539 --> 01:01:47.291
Well done to all of you!

605
01:01:47.374 --> 01:01:50.043
You are the strongest
warriors in Africa!

606
01:01:50.961 --> 01:01:52.671
Welcome to the King's Guard.

607
01:02:06.101 --> 01:02:07.394
Agojie!

608
01:02:07.978 --> 01:02:09.021
Agojie!

609
01:02:09.730 --> 01:02:10.730
Agojie!

610
01:02:17.821 --> 01:02:19.156
Hey. be still.

611
01:02:22.201 --> 01:02:23.201
Thank you.

612
01:02:24.244 --> 01:02:27.831
Why did you return to help
Fumbe? You could have lost.

613
01:02:27.915 --> 01:02:31.084
Fumbe is my friend.
I want her to stay.

614
01:02:31.668 --> 01:02:36.298
- To stay. she must pass the test.
- To be useful. she must stand on her own.

615
01:02:38.425 --> 01:02:40.969
You would not help
your friend. <i>Miganon?</i>

616
01:02:41.053 --> 01:02:44.640
Amenza? I would step on
her head to win a footrace.

617
01:02:48.936 --> 01:02:52.272
Your first scars. The
mark of a warrior.

618
01:02:53.857 --> 01:02:54.857
You see?

619
01:02:57.694 --> 01:02:59.696
You will have many more.

620
01:03:10.582 --> 01:03:11.583
Make sure

621
01:03:12.960 --> 01:03:14.878
all the thorns come out.

622
01:03:14.962 --> 01:03:15.962
Here. Here.

623
01:03:17.548 --> 01:03:18.548
Here.

624
01:03:20.717 --> 01:03:21.885
What is this?

625
01:03:24.638 --> 01:03:27.224
My father used to call
it the devil's mark.

626
01:03:28.016 --> 01:03:31.270
It was there when he chose
me from the orphanage.

627
01:03:32.145 --> 01:03:33.313
You are an orphan?

628
01:03:35.899 --> 01:03:39.236
- But your father...
- He took me in.

629
01:03:40.028 --> 01:03:42.656
I guess I didn't turn out to
be the daughter he wanted.

630
01:04:06.638 --> 01:04:07.890
Nani?

631
01:04:13.478 --> 01:04:16.023
- What did you do with it?
- With what?

632
01:04:23.280 --> 01:04:25.115
- You told me never to tell you.
- I'm asking.

633
01:04:25.199 --> 01:04:27.618
You said you would ask.
and you made me swear.

634
01:04:27.701 --> 01:04:29.077
Amenza!

635
01:04:30.913 --> 01:04:34.291
I am not your servant. Nanisca.

636
01:04:46.261 --> 01:04:49.056
- I gave her to the missionaries.
- What missionaries?

637
01:04:49.139 --> 01:04:50.974
The ones we passed on the road.

638
01:04:51.058 --> 01:04:53.143
- Where did they take her?
- I have no way to know.

639
01:04:53.227 --> 01:04:56.230
- What direction did they go?
- I followed your order.

640
01:04:57.314 --> 01:04:59.566
To free you of the burden.

641
01:04:59.650 --> 01:05:02.236
And I chose to give her away.

642
01:05:02.319 --> 01:05:05.155
- And that is all you know?
- Yes! I do not lie to you.

643
01:05:07.950 --> 01:05:11.370
Why do you ask these
questions after all this time?

644
01:05:14.748 --> 01:05:17.417
Because Nawi is an orphan?

645
01:05:20.045 --> 01:05:23.257
You couldn't possibly
think that she...

646
01:05:26.552 --> 01:05:27.719
Of course not.

647
01:05:29.513 --> 01:05:30.513
No.

648
01:05:41.942 --> 01:05:44.820
The gods are not that cruel.

649
01:05:53.996 --> 01:05:56.707
Speak my language when
you are in my palace.

650
01:05:58.917 --> 01:06:02.629
Your wife Shante. she said
you seek an end to the trade.

651
01:06:04.882 --> 01:06:09.469
She does not speak for me. And she
will be punished for thinking she does.

652
01:06:11.930 --> 01:06:14.892
She says this is your general's
wish and perhaps not yours.

653
01:06:14.975 --> 01:06:17.728
My generals obey my wishes.

654
01:06:17.811 --> 01:06:21.106
So you wish to sell palm oil.

655
01:06:21.190 --> 01:06:23.400
I wish for my people to prosper.

656
01:06:24.318 --> 01:06:26.028
as those of your land do.

657
01:06:26.111 --> 01:06:32.326
Ghezo. the people in my lands
prosper because of the slave trade.

658
01:06:32.826 --> 01:06:35.621
And this very same
trade has made you rich.

659
01:06:36.205 --> 01:06:38.498
As rich as the King of England.

660
01:06:39.708 --> 01:06:43.128
You stop the trade.
you will be nothing.

661
01:06:44.046 --> 01:06:47.633
King. maybe. but king of mud.

662
01:06:48.300 --> 01:06:51.637
All of these captains will
take their business elsewhere.

663
01:06:52.429 --> 01:06:54.556
The business of
selling Africans?

664
01:06:56.767 --> 01:06:59.186
You will be unprotected.

665
01:07:00.062 --> 01:07:01.355
Unprotected?

666
01:07:07.486 --> 01:07:13.242
You know. I am under no illusion that
you see us as anything but a commodity.

667
01:07:16.495 --> 01:07:17.829
But I am a king.

668
01:07:19.623 --> 01:07:21.625
With or without your respect.

669
01:07:23.502 --> 01:07:26.380
And if you are no longer
a necessity to me.

670
01:07:28.507 --> 01:07:30.592
you. too. are unprotected.

671
01:07:51.321 --> 01:07:52.321
Malik.

672
01:07:56.535 --> 01:07:57.535
Nawi.

673
01:07:58.370 --> 01:07:59.955
- May I come in?
- No.

674
01:08:00.747 --> 01:08:02.875
No man may cross the palm line.

675
01:08:03.834 --> 01:08:06.670
In Brazil. foreign men may
look on the king's women?

676
01:08:06.753 --> 01:08:12.676
In Brazil. women cover their bodies
with long sleeves. long skirts.

677
01:08:13.302 --> 01:08:14.720
Then how do they run?

678
01:08:20.559 --> 01:08:22.895
We make camp outside
the walls tonight.

679
01:08:22.978 --> 01:08:24.313
Come to see me.

680
01:08:24.395 --> 01:08:26.523
Tonight we take our blood oath.

681
01:08:26.607 --> 01:08:27.607
Afterward.

682
01:08:29.234 --> 01:08:31.819
If you wish for a girl
to come to your tent.

683
01:08:31.904 --> 01:08:33.947
there are girls you
can pay in the market.

684
01:08:34.031 --> 01:08:36.783
No. no. I just want
to talk to you.

685
01:08:38.410 --> 01:08:39.410
Malik!

686
01:08:43.582 --> 01:08:45.000
Will you come to see me?

687
01:09:35.175 --> 01:09:36.510
Agojie!

688
01:09:39.220 --> 01:09:40.930
Blood of our sisters!

689
01:09:43.100 --> 01:09:44.560
<i>Make us invincible</i>

690
01:09:47.104 --> 01:09:48.647
<i>You live for me</i>

691
01:09:49.857 --> 01:09:51.316
<i>And I for you</i>

692
01:09:53.527 --> 01:09:54.903
<i>Blood of our sisters</i>

693
01:09:56.488 --> 01:09:58.907
<i>Make us invincible</i>

694
01:10:03.370 --> 01:10:06.039
<i>You live for me and I for you</i>

695
01:10:06.582 --> 01:10:10.794
<i>You live for me and
I for you Agojie</i>

696
01:10:16.633 --> 01:10:18.093
You are now my sister.

697
01:10:18.635 --> 01:10:20.637
I will be proud
to fight with you.

698
01:10:21.346 --> 01:10:22.890
I want you to teach me.

699
01:10:23.432 --> 01:10:25.225
Like the <i>Miganon </i>teaches you.

700
01:10:26.018 --> 01:10:27.686
I also want to be great.

701
01:10:28.645 --> 01:10:31.648
To be great. you must focus.

702
01:10:32.274 --> 01:10:35.194
- There can be no distractions.
- I will.

703
01:10:38.071 --> 01:10:42.326
At the test. I saw the man
from Brazil wave to you.

704
01:10:43.660 --> 01:10:44.786
You know this man?

705
01:10:47.581 --> 01:10:49.541
I came across him in the jungle.

706
01:10:50.125 --> 01:10:51.585
"In the jungle."

707
01:10:54.087 --> 01:10:56.215
So. what. you have
feelings for him?

708
01:10:56.798 --> 01:10:59.593
I have no way to know
how I feel about him.

709
01:11:01.762 --> 01:11:03.263
You want me to teach you.

710
01:11:07.768 --> 01:11:09.186
You are powerful.

711
01:11:09.978 --> 01:11:11.396
More than you even know.

712
01:11:12.564 --> 01:11:14.399
Do not give your power away.

713
01:11:19.279 --> 01:11:20.280
You mean to love?

714
01:11:20.948 --> 01:11:22.616
Love makes you weak.

715
01:11:23.242 --> 01:11:24.701
You really believe that?

716
01:11:27.955 --> 01:11:29.414
You have never loved?

717
01:11:31.917 --> 01:11:33.836
I will be <i>Miganon </i>one day.

718
01:11:36.588 --> 01:11:37.881
You cannot have both.

719
01:11:38.966 --> 01:11:40.300
Will that be enough?

720
01:11:41.093 --> 01:11:43.011
This is the life we have chosen.

721
01:11:44.012 --> 01:11:46.515
We each survive in our own way.

722
01:11:46.598 --> 01:11:48.183
You will find yours.

723
01:12:02.823 --> 01:12:04.783
<i>My mother was a slave.</i>

724
01:12:04.867 --> 01:12:07.494
That is all I ever
knew of African people.

725
01:12:08.203 --> 01:12:14.585
I never dreamed that we
were kings and warriors.

726
01:12:17.504 --> 01:12:19.423
But now?

727
01:12:20.215 --> 01:12:22.217
I see the majesty.

728
01:12:24.094 --> 01:12:25.470
I see the beauty.

729
01:12:26.763 --> 01:12:28.432
I think you are a good man.

730
01:12:29.183 --> 01:12:31.768
You must not ally
yourself with slavers.

731
01:12:32.936 --> 01:12:34.479
We grew up together.

732
01:12:34.563 --> 01:12:36.940
But does he see our
beauty as you do?

733
01:12:47.784 --> 01:12:49.494
Nawi. the Oyo are coming.

734
01:12:50.078 --> 01:12:50.954
We are ready.

735
01:12:51.038 --> 01:12:53.123
No. not just the Oyo.

736
01:12:53.624 --> 01:12:55.083
Other tribes too.

737
01:12:55.751 --> 01:12:57.544
I heard the general plotting.

738
01:12:59.129 --> 01:13:00.631
We must tell the <i>Miganon.</i>

739
01:13:01.340 --> 01:13:03.300
- I must get back.
- Nawi. wait.

740
01:13:04.676 --> 01:13:06.678
Tomorrow we are going to leave.

741
01:13:20.567 --> 01:13:21.860
This is Ogou.

742
01:13:23.403 --> 01:13:25.030
He is courage and strength.

743
01:13:25.781 --> 01:13:27.991
Perhaps he will
bring you back to us.

744
01:13:30.953 --> 01:13:32.788
I have nothing to give to you.

745
01:13:54.017 --> 01:13:55.477
I will take you back.

746
01:14:15.581 --> 01:14:16.581
<i>Miganon.</i>

747
01:14:19.835 --> 01:14:21.378
I have heard something.

748
01:14:22.171 --> 01:14:24.256
One of the men that came
to the palace. Malik.

749
01:14:24.339 --> 01:14:27.718
he says the Oyo general is growing
his army with other tribes.

750
01:14:27.801 --> 01:14:29.678
They will march on Dahomey.

751
01:14:30.262 --> 01:14:32.222
The Oyo have given them courage.

752
01:14:35.184 --> 01:14:38.520
Where were you speaking
with this man. Malik?

753
01:14:39.730 --> 01:14:41.690
He spoke to me
through the palm line.

754
01:14:41.773 --> 01:14:44.568
On the night you swear
loyalty to your sisters.

755
01:14:44.651 --> 01:14:46.695
you speak in secret
with a slaver?

756
01:14:46.778 --> 01:14:49.531
He's not a slaver. His
mother was Dahomey.

757
01:14:49.615 --> 01:14:50.782
You defend him?

758
01:14:53.076 --> 01:14:54.703
Is that knife a gift?

759
01:14:56.955 --> 01:14:58.248
Where have you been?

760
01:14:59.708 --> 01:15:01.835
- I have been nowhere.
- Come here.

761
01:15:04.505 --> 01:15:05.505
Here.

762
01:15:18.977 --> 01:15:20.979
You are an Agojie.

763
01:15:22.189 --> 01:15:23.982
You cannot be with a man.

764
01:15:25.025 --> 01:15:27.986
Do you think you are so special
that I will not put you out?

765
01:15:28.070 --> 01:15:29.154
Because I will.

766
01:15:29.238 --> 01:15:32.491
- I do not think I am special.
- Do not bow your head.

767
01:15:32.574 --> 01:15:34.368
Do not.

768
01:15:35.994 --> 01:15:40.457
I know your arrogance. You continue to do
as you please. You disregard the rules.

769
01:15:40.541 --> 01:15:42.417
What do you want from me?

770
01:15:44.044 --> 01:15:46.797
I proved myself
today. I am the best!

771
01:15:46.880 --> 01:15:49.216
It is not enough to be the best!

772
01:15:50.592 --> 01:15:52.928
Your arrogance and your
stupidity will get you caught.

773
01:15:53.011 --> 01:15:54.555
I am not you!

774
01:15:55.389 --> 01:15:59.017
Izogie told me that you were
captured. That will never be me!

775
01:15:59.101 --> 01:16:01.436
I was raped many
times each night.

776
01:16:04.857 --> 01:16:08.151
When they would come.
I wished only to die.

777
01:16:10.779 --> 01:16:12.614
They took it all away.

778
01:16:13.198 --> 01:16:14.700
Everything I knew.

779
01:16:15.868 --> 01:16:18.787
And when I finally
escaped. I was with child.

780
01:16:20.205 --> 01:16:21.957
A child of those men.

781
01:16:23.625 --> 01:16:27.629
I would have to leave my sisters
forever. so I had to hide.

782
01:16:29.631 --> 01:16:31.008
I bathed alone.

783
01:16:31.592 --> 01:16:32.885
And my belly grew.

784
01:16:48.108 --> 01:16:49.318
<i>It was a girl.</i>

785
01:16:50.068 --> 01:16:52.279
<i>I told Amenza. "Take it away."</i>

786
01:16:54.072 --> 01:16:57.075
<i>But the blood. it kept coming.</i>

787
01:16:57.159 --> 01:17:01.622
And Amenza ran away to find
medicine. and she left me with her.

788
01:17:04.541 --> 01:17:06.335
So I did something.

789
01:17:35.113 --> 01:17:38.951
<i>I made a cut on the
back of the left arm.</i>

790
01:17:39.493 --> 01:17:41.662
and I pressed a tooth into it.

791
01:17:42.829 --> 01:17:44.081
A shark's tooth.

792
01:17:51.713 --> 01:17:53.006
It isn't me.

793
01:20:04.972 --> 01:20:07.766
They are a day's journey
from our plateau.

794
01:20:08.308 --> 01:20:10.060
They will set up camp there.

795
01:20:12.104 --> 01:20:15.482
They expect us to defend
ourselves from behind our walls.

796
01:20:15.983 --> 01:20:17.609
We are greatly outnumbered.

797
01:20:17.693 --> 01:20:23.282
Their size makes them arrogant
and slow. like their guns.

798
01:20:38.922 --> 01:20:42.009
But you don't need a
gun to use gunpowder.

799
01:20:43.844 --> 01:20:45.679
<i>You just need a spark.</i>

800
01:20:47.472 --> 01:20:52.394
<i>Sometimes a termite can
take down an elephant.</i>

801
01:20:53.979 --> 01:20:56.315
<i>We will bring the war to them.</i>

802
01:21:01.403 --> 01:21:02.779
Agojie!

803
01:21:54.998 --> 01:22:01.088
For 90 years. Dahomey has lived
under the thumb of the Oyo!

804
01:22:02.506 --> 01:22:06.552
When it rains.
our ancestors weep

805
01:22:06.635 --> 01:22:10.222
for the pain we have felt
in the dark hulls of ships

806
01:22:10.305 --> 01:22:12.641
bound for distant shores!

807
01:22:15.394 --> 01:22:19.356
When the wind blows.
our ancestors push us

808
01:22:19.439 --> 01:22:23.485
to march into battle against
those who enslave us!

809
01:22:24.695 --> 01:22:26.071
When it thunders.

810
01:22:26.822 --> 01:22:31.827
our ancestors demand we rip the
shackles of doubt from our minds

811
01:22:31.910 --> 01:22:33.745
<i>and fight with courage!</i>

812
01:22:35.497 --> 01:22:38.834
We fight not just for
today. but for the future.

813
01:22:39.835 --> 01:22:43.630
We are the spear of victory.

814
01:22:44.506 --> 01:22:46.884
We are the blade of freedom.

815
01:22:47.634 --> 01:22:50.345
We are Dahomey!

816
01:22:51.180 --> 01:22:52.472
Agojie!

817
01:22:53.140 --> 01:22:54.308
Agojie!

818
01:22:55.350 --> 01:22:56.351
<i>Agojie!</i>

819
01:24:15.973 --> 01:24:17.766
We are under attack! Attack!

820
01:24:27.025 --> 01:24:28.735
Grab your weapons!

821
01:24:29.319 --> 01:24:30.571
We are Oyo!

822
01:28:21.552 --> 01:28:22.803
Where is Oba?

823
01:28:25.931 --> 01:28:27.266
Where is Oba?

824
01:28:40.988 --> 01:28:41.988
Fall back!

825
01:28:43.198 --> 01:28:45.701
Fall back! Oyo. fall back!

826
01:29:19.193 --> 01:29:20.485
Grab the Agojie.

827
01:29:21.153 --> 01:29:22.153
Oyo. move!

828
01:29:23.572 --> 01:29:25.157
Oba wants the Agojie.

829
01:29:25.699 --> 01:29:27.242
Move. move. move!

830
01:29:42.466 --> 01:29:44.218
They are retreating!

831
01:30:11.286 --> 01:30:14.790
You fought well.
my young sister.

832
01:30:19.461 --> 01:30:21.046
Now you must rest.

833
01:30:33.016 --> 01:30:34.560
She is not here.

834
01:30:35.769 --> 01:30:37.563
No one has seen her.

835
01:31:22.191 --> 01:31:23.191
Fumbe.

836
01:31:24.443 --> 01:31:25.485
I failed.

837
01:31:25.569 --> 01:31:28.322
No. You stayed alive.

838
01:31:32.534 --> 01:31:34.036
You are not tied to anyone.

839
01:31:35.787 --> 01:31:36.997
Go over.

840
01:31:38.999 --> 01:31:40.542
Do you want to live?

841
01:31:45.380 --> 01:31:46.423
Now.

842
01:32:06.735 --> 01:32:08.862
We need to buy passage.

843
01:32:09.613 --> 01:32:11.114
We are not going home?

844
01:32:11.198 --> 01:32:12.449
We have lost.

845
01:32:12.533 --> 01:32:15.077
At home we are dead men.

846
01:32:18.038 --> 01:32:22.668
Put this one on display. The
bids will be higher for soldiers.

847
01:32:27.798 --> 01:32:28.799
Move!

848
01:32:30.050 --> 01:32:31.468
I said move.

849
01:32:54.658 --> 01:32:55.658
Move! Back!

850
01:32:55.701 --> 01:32:57.369
Make space for one more.

851
01:33:14.344 --> 01:33:15.387
Izogie.

852
01:33:19.141 --> 01:33:20.350
Come. Sit.

853
01:33:21.268 --> 01:33:22.269
Sit.

854
01:33:35.490 --> 01:33:36.491
Eat.

855
01:33:37.576 --> 01:33:39.870
We will need our
strength to escape.

856
01:33:43.707 --> 01:33:45.542
My arm is broken.

857
01:33:46.251 --> 01:33:47.961
I know what I must do.

858
01:33:49.630 --> 01:33:51.590
What the <i>Miganon</i> said.

859
01:33:54.510 --> 01:33:56.386
We will slit our throats.

860
01:33:58.388 --> 01:34:00.015
We will not.

861
01:34:02.518 --> 01:34:05.646
"Fear not. Face it head-on.

862
01:34:08.524 --> 01:34:10.943
Relentlessly we will fight."

863
01:34:15.197 --> 01:34:16.823
You are Izogie.

864
01:34:17.616 --> 01:34:19.034
You said it.

865
01:34:19.868 --> 01:34:22.412
"Relentlessly we will fight."

866
01:34:23.830 --> 01:34:24.831
Come on!

867
01:34:46.311 --> 01:34:47.855
Push it back together.

868
01:35:14.298 --> 01:35:16.550
You are strong for a little fly.

869
01:35:27.311 --> 01:35:28.395
Now what?

870
01:35:57.674 --> 01:35:59.635
<i>They were taking us
to the barracoons.</i>

871
01:35:59.718 --> 01:36:00.928
How many others?

872
01:36:01.929 --> 01:36:03.597
Three. I think.

873
01:36:03.680 --> 01:36:04.723
Izogie?

874
01:36:06.225 --> 01:36:07.768
I did not see her.

875
01:36:09.561 --> 01:36:11.647
Nawi said to throw
myself off the wagon.

876
01:36:12.397 --> 01:36:13.482
Nawi?

877
01:36:19.196 --> 01:36:21.406
<i>Miganon. Ajahi.</i>

878
01:36:21.490 --> 01:36:23.283
The king requests you.

879
01:36:23.909 --> 01:36:27.621
I have brought you here
because I have chosen <i>Kpojito.</i>

880
01:36:28.580 --> 01:36:30.707
<i>Kpojito</i> is beloved
of the people.

881
01:36:30.791 --> 01:36:34.711
She must be deserving of their
admiration and their trust.

882
01:36:34.795 --> 01:36:38.841
We must share the same
vision for our future.

883
01:36:38.924 --> 01:36:40.425
A bold future.

884
01:36:41.260 --> 01:36:42.511
For that reason.

885
01:36:42.594 --> 01:36:44.346
I have chosen Nanisca.

886
01:36:49.226 --> 01:36:51.520
- She is a common soldier!
- Will you sit down?

887
01:36:51.603 --> 01:36:53.480
- Ruined by the enemy!
- Sit down and be quiet!

888
01:36:53.564 --> 01:36:54.940
Shante.

889
01:36:58.318 --> 01:37:01.446
Kelu. Efe. go and talk
to her. Go. go. go.

890
01:37:03.323 --> 01:37:04.741
We will celebrate.

891
01:37:05.576 --> 01:37:09.496
We will bring the city to the
palace. and we will have a big feast.

892
01:37:09.580 --> 01:37:10.580
Go and prepare.

893
01:37:17.045 --> 01:37:18.088
Well done.

894
01:37:31.935 --> 01:37:35.105
My king. it is a great honor.

895
01:37:35.189 --> 01:37:37.691
But perhaps it is too soon.

896
01:37:37.774 --> 01:37:40.944
When we have lost so many soldiers.
and the people are grieving...

897
01:37:41.028 --> 01:37:42.029
Grieving?

898
01:37:42.988 --> 01:37:46.992
No one is grieving. We have won.
We have thrown off the yoke.

899
01:37:47.075 --> 01:37:49.494
My king. I wish to
seek our lost Agojie.

900
01:37:49.578 --> 01:37:52.080
Some were taken captive. They
will be sold. used by the men.

901
01:37:52.164 --> 01:37:53.624
The moment you seek is here.

902
01:37:55.042 --> 01:37:58.337
The few have been sacrificed for
the many. Now we must move forward.

903
01:37:58.420 --> 01:38:00.088
I can go alone. Let me try.

904
01:38:00.172 --> 01:38:01.590
You disobey me. Nanisca.

905
01:38:03.133 --> 01:38:06.011
Are you confusing my
admiration for weakness?

906
01:38:07.304 --> 01:38:08.805
I am your king.

907
01:38:09.848 --> 01:38:11.266
Let me tell you:

908
01:38:11.350 --> 01:38:13.602
You will not seek
out those captives.

909
01:38:14.311 --> 01:38:16.188
You must stay by my side

910
01:38:16.271 --> 01:38:18.690
and take the honor I bestow you.

911
01:38:19.983 --> 01:38:21.860
Do not force my anger.

912
01:38:37.417 --> 01:38:39.503
<i>In the morning. they will come.</i>

913
01:38:39.586 --> 01:38:41.630
- Move it! Move it!
- Get back! Back!

914
01:38:41.713 --> 01:38:44.466
- Back!
- Move it!

915
01:38:44.550 --> 01:38:45.551
Stay back!

916
01:38:56.061 --> 01:38:57.062
Move!

917
01:38:57.855 --> 01:39:00.107
<i>They will take the Agojie first.</i>

918
01:39:22.754 --> 01:39:24.131
On your feet.

919
01:39:33.515 --> 01:39:35.642
<i>We must have patience.</i>

920
01:39:42.065 --> 01:39:44.443
<i>When we are brought
to the block.</i>

921
01:39:44.526 --> 01:39:45.819
<i>we will be unshackled.</i>

922
01:39:46.820 --> 01:39:48.655
<i>We will have our legs.</i>

923
01:39:59.416 --> 01:40:02.211
<i>We must not let them
see my arm is broken.</i>

924
01:40:20.103 --> 01:40:22.981
<i>When we are sold. that
will be the moment.</i>

925
01:40:23.524 --> 01:40:25.317
<i>You will make a distraction.</i>

926
01:40:25.400 --> 01:40:27.152
I give you 90 for this one.

927
01:40:27.236 --> 01:40:28.529
120.

928
01:40:30.280 --> 01:40:33.158
Oba. you said you would
be good to me here.

929
01:40:33.242 --> 01:40:35.327
It will go to the
highest bidder.

930
01:40:35.410 --> 01:40:38.247
<i>We will each disarm
a guard. and run.</i>

931
01:40:38.330 --> 01:40:41.458
<i>Do not stop until
you reach the water.</i>

932
01:40:41.542 --> 01:40:42.960
150 réis.

933
01:40:50.217 --> 01:40:51.134
Nawi!

934
01:40:51.218 --> 01:40:53.387
What the hell are you doing!

935
01:40:53.470 --> 01:40:55.514
What I came here to do!

936
01:40:55.597 --> 01:40:57.808
You call them savages?
It is you who is savage!

937
01:40:57.891 --> 01:41:02.020
Stay out of this! Count yourself
lucky you are not on the block!

938
01:41:24.042 --> 01:41:25.043
Stay where you are!

939
01:41:43.937 --> 01:41:44.937
No.

940
01:41:48.275 --> 01:41:49.443
No!

941
01:41:53.697 --> 01:41:54.697
No!

942
01:42:01.246 --> 01:42:02.539
Izogie.

943
01:42:03.415 --> 01:42:06.502
Come on. Come on. Come on.

944
01:42:07.794 --> 01:42:08.921
Get up.

945
01:42:09.546 --> 01:42:12.966
No. Izogie. get up.

946
01:42:13.050 --> 01:42:14.218
Please. Izogie.

947
01:42:19.389 --> 01:42:22.518
No. No. No! No.

948
01:42:22.601 --> 01:42:23.852
I'm sorry.

949
01:42:23.936 --> 01:42:25.062
Nawi.

950
01:42:27.814 --> 01:42:29.733
You move like a sloth.

951
01:42:30.984 --> 01:42:32.319
I'm sorry.

952
01:42:32.402 --> 01:42:34.279
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

953
01:42:34.363 --> 01:42:36.490
Let's go. Let's go.

954
01:42:41.203 --> 01:42:42.246
Izogie?

955
01:42:42.996 --> 01:42:45.040
Izogie. Izogie.

956
01:42:49.545 --> 01:42:51.713
You get away from her!

957
01:42:51.797 --> 01:42:53.298
Get away!

958
01:43:11.483 --> 01:43:12.943
If you want this one.

959
01:43:13.861 --> 01:43:15.529
100 réis.

960
01:43:35.424 --> 01:43:36.800
- What are you doing?
- Move aside.

961
01:43:36.884 --> 01:43:39.428
You know what the king will
do to you if you defy him.

962
01:43:39.511 --> 01:43:42.681
You want to be expelled. or
worse? No. no. I cannot stand by.

963
01:43:42.764 --> 01:43:44.349
I know what it is.

964
01:43:45.184 --> 01:43:46.685
In the dream.

965
01:43:48.187 --> 01:43:50.439
The beast I am so frightened of.

966
01:43:56.361 --> 01:43:57.779
It is me.

967
01:44:02.910 --> 01:44:05.746
It is that girl who was silenced

968
01:44:05.829 --> 01:44:08.957
in those shackles by those men.

969
01:44:12.377 --> 01:44:14.171
I've hidden her away.

970
01:44:15.047 --> 01:44:16.924
I have denied her pain.

971
01:44:21.428 --> 01:44:23.931
But I'm going to hear her now.

972
01:44:28.101 --> 01:44:30.562
- I have to try to save her.
- No.

973
01:44:32.481 --> 01:44:33.649
Please.

974
01:45:59.860 --> 01:46:02.654
It is not safe for us.
I brought you clothes.

975
01:46:02.738 --> 01:46:04.865
I will sneak you
out at nightfall.

976
01:46:04.948 --> 01:46:07.409
- Do you own me now?
- Of course not.

977
01:46:07.492 --> 01:46:09.453
- Get out!
- I am trying to protect you.

978
01:46:09.536 --> 01:46:10.412
By locking me in?

979
01:46:10.495 --> 01:46:13.707
Do you know what they would do
to you? A white man was killed.

980
01:46:18.754 --> 01:46:20.380
You have the key now.

981
01:46:22.090 --> 01:46:24.301
You can choose when
the lock is turned.

982
01:47:28.991 --> 01:47:31.994
My mother guided me
here to find myself.

983
01:47:33.745 --> 01:47:35.205
And I found you.

984
01:47:36.039 --> 01:47:39.585
I have booked passage on a
cargo ship bound for England.

985
01:47:41.044 --> 01:47:42.379
I want to keep you safe.

986
01:47:47.551 --> 01:47:51.305
My heart has many scars.

987
01:48:08.780 --> 01:48:09.823
Husband.

988
01:48:10.407 --> 01:48:13.285
Please accept my deepest apologies
for questioning your will.

989
01:48:14.953 --> 01:48:16.205
What do you want?

990
01:48:16.288 --> 01:48:17.456
Move. my friend.

991
01:48:17.539 --> 01:48:19.333
The wives are whispering.

992
01:48:20.250 --> 01:48:23.045
- I told Tanonu what they say...
- Have I not told you not to discuss

993
01:48:23.128 --> 01:48:25.297
my business with the
wives? Have I not told you?

994
01:48:25.380 --> 01:48:27.633
My king. please forgive me.

995
01:48:27.716 --> 01:48:29.635
Nanisca's gone to Ouidah

996
01:48:29.718 --> 01:48:31.929
with the <i>Migan</i> and a
number of her soldiers.

997
01:48:32.012 --> 01:48:33.931
We must postpone the feast.

998
01:48:34.014 --> 01:48:35.891
No. no. The people gossip.

999
01:48:35.974 --> 01:48:38.769
You cannot postpone it now.
not without looking weak.

1000
01:49:20.018 --> 01:49:21.270
Where are the others?

1001
01:49:23.063 --> 01:49:24.982
Izogie was killed. <i>Miganon</i>.

1002
01:49:26.275 --> 01:49:27.609
Nawi is gone.

1003
01:49:45.627 --> 01:49:47.880
There will be no prisoners.

1004
01:49:47.963 --> 01:49:50.924
Burn their whole
trade to the ground.

1005
01:50:18.952 --> 01:50:20.412
Sound the alarm!

1006
01:50:41.225 --> 01:50:43.227
Nawi. Nawi.

1007
01:50:43.310 --> 01:50:44.561
I need to come in.

1008
01:50:47.439 --> 01:50:50.400
- We must go.
- My sisters have come.

1009
01:50:50.484 --> 01:50:51.693
I have to help them.

1010
01:50:53.070 --> 01:50:54.363
Then I will help you.

1011
01:50:54.446 --> 01:50:55.614
No.

1012
01:50:55.697 --> 01:50:56.697
Malik.

1013
01:50:57.950 --> 01:50:59.368
You must go.

1014
01:51:05.457 --> 01:51:06.959
Your clothes are bloody.

1015
01:51:10.838 --> 01:51:12.464
You can wear these.

1016
01:51:20.305 --> 01:51:22.015
I will take care of him.

1017
01:51:23.475 --> 01:51:25.185
I will be on the beach.

1018
01:52:03.098 --> 01:52:04.516
I want Oba.

1019
01:52:22.534 --> 01:52:24.203
Hurry up. this way. this way!

1020
01:52:24.286 --> 01:52:25.746
Move. damn it!

1021
01:52:25.829 --> 01:52:27.122
Malik!

1022
01:52:27.706 --> 01:52:28.790
Push!

1023
01:52:28.874 --> 01:52:31.335
Bring a boat! I need a boat!

1024
01:52:34.463 --> 01:52:35.589
No. no. no!

1025
01:52:36.632 --> 01:52:37.633
Malik!

1026
01:52:43.764 --> 01:52:45.057
Malik! In!

1027
01:52:59.446 --> 01:53:00.446
Malik. no!

1028
01:53:00.489 --> 01:53:02.533
Loose me! Loose me!

1029
01:53:03.408 --> 01:53:04.868
No. No.

1030
01:53:04.952 --> 01:53:06.078
No!

1031
01:53:06.161 --> 01:53:08.580
Malik! Malik. no!

1032
01:53:11.083 --> 01:53:12.125
No!

1033
01:55:28.804 --> 01:55:30.973
You do not remember me.

1034
01:55:34.852 --> 01:55:35.853
Now...

1035
01:55:36.520 --> 01:55:38.272
you will never forget.

1036
01:57:16.453 --> 01:57:18.205
Agojie!

1037
01:57:19.540 --> 01:57:21.041
Agojie!

1038
01:57:21.917 --> 01:57:23.752
Agojie!

1039
01:57:35.597 --> 01:57:38.350
Come! We cannot stay
here. Get in the boat!

1040
01:58:25.689 --> 01:58:28.692
Shante. well done.
You deserve it.

1041
01:58:45.876 --> 01:58:48.962
Nanisca! Nanisca! Nanisca!

1042
01:58:49.546 --> 01:58:53.300
Nanisca! Nanisca! Nanisca!

1043
01:59:31.630 --> 01:59:34.925
You disobey your king. Nanisca.

1044
01:59:36.927 --> 01:59:39.263
I will resign my command.

1045
01:59:50.774 --> 01:59:52.317
People of Dahomey!

1046
01:59:54.611 --> 01:59:57.197
We have ended the reign
of the Oyo Empire!

1047
02:00:04.705 --> 02:00:07.958
Look upon the faces of the
warriors. Look at them.

1048
02:00:09.376 --> 02:00:11.253
Many never thought it possible.

1049
02:00:12.337 --> 02:00:13.797
But we believed.

1050
02:00:15.382 --> 02:00:17.259
That is what makes
a great leader.

1051
02:00:18.594 --> 02:00:20.387
Seeing what others do not.

1052
02:00:21.096 --> 02:00:25.100
The Europeans and the
Americans have seen

1053
02:00:25.184 --> 02:00:27.436
if you want to hold
a people in chains...

1054
02:00:28.937 --> 02:00:32.232
one must first convince them
that they are meant to be bound.

1055
02:00:33.734 --> 02:00:37.154
We joined them in becoming
our own oppressor.

1056
02:00:37.237 --> 02:00:38.447
But no more.

1057
02:00:41.033 --> 02:00:42.033
No more.

1058
02:00:44.578 --> 02:00:46.371
We are a warrior people.

1059
02:00:47.581 --> 02:00:49.583
And there is power in our mind.

1060
02:00:50.751 --> 02:00:51.835
in our unity.

1061
02:00:52.586 --> 02:00:53.629
in our culture.

1062
02:00:54.755 --> 02:00:56.715
If we understand that power.

1063
02:00:57.341 --> 02:00:58.759
we will be limitless.

1064
02:01:00.093 --> 02:01:01.386
My people.

1065
02:01:02.387 --> 02:01:04.389
this is a vision I will lead.

1066
02:01:06.141 --> 02:01:07.976
It is a vision that is shared.

1067
02:01:13.815 --> 02:01:15.484
Heroes of Dahomey!

1068
02:01:16.818 --> 02:01:19.738
Behold. the bravest
of the brave.

1069
02:01:20.864 --> 02:01:22.783
appointed by King Ghezo.

1070
02:01:22.866 --> 02:01:25.994
elevated to the sacred
title of <i>Kpojito:</i>

1071
02:01:26.662 --> 02:01:29.248
Nanisca. the Woman King.

1072
02:02:24.052 --> 02:02:27.097
An offering for Izogie.

1073
02:02:27.181 --> 02:02:29.766
She does not want that water.

1074
02:02:30.893 --> 02:02:32.102
She wants this.

1075
02:02:49.536 --> 02:02:51.496
In my blood is the
blood of a killer.

1076
02:02:56.710 --> 02:02:58.962
A man who gave you so much pain.

1077
02:03:04.301 --> 02:03:05.594
I am sorry.

1078
02:03:15.896 --> 02:03:17.814
You are Agojie.

1079
02:03:29.952 --> 02:03:31.495
I am sorry.

1080
02:03:33.997 --> 02:03:35.123
I left you.

1081
02:03:39.670 --> 02:03:41.421
I was not brave enough.

1082
02:03:45.759 --> 02:03:48.887
But you survived because
you are meant to be here.

1083
02:03:58.313 --> 02:04:01.191
It is not your fault
what happened to me.

1084
02:04:04.194 --> 02:04:05.195
You...

1085
02:04:07.364 --> 02:04:09.533
are not the thing that hurt me.

1086
02:04:14.705 --> 02:04:16.623
You are Nawi.

1087
02:04:20.794 --> 02:04:22.754
You are my daughter.

1088
02:04:25.048 --> 02:04:26.258
I am sorry.

1089
02:05:56.974 --> 02:05:58.475
Mother. will you dance?

1090
02:09:38.529 --> 02:09:40.489
Sisters in blood:

1091
02:09:41.240 --> 02:09:42.533
You fall...

1092
02:09:43.283 --> 02:09:45.744
and now you rise.

1093
02:09:48.372 --> 02:09:49.998
Dance with us.

1094
02:09:51.083 --> 02:09:52.835
Be with us.

1095
02:09:53.627 --> 02:09:55.420
You live for me

1096
02:09:56.296 --> 02:09:58.423
and I for you.

1097
02:10:02.636 --> 02:10:03.762
Izogie.

1098
02:10:05.597 --> 02:10:06.723
Ode.

1099
02:10:08.642 --> 02:10:09.642
Esi.

1100
02:10:10.519 --> 02:10:11.603
Yoshe.

1101
02:10:12.729 --> 02:10:13.772
Alekko.

1102
02:10:14.648 --> 02:10:15.648
Kesia.

1103
02:10:17.067 --> 02:10:18.193
<i>Breonna.</i>
